
NPM --> Node package manager

It is a tool used to install and manage packages (libraries) for Node.js projects.
you can think of npm as a large online store of JavaScript libraries.

Example libraries: Express , Mongoose ,Lodash ,Axios ,React etc

Express and Mongoose are stored in the npm registry (an online database of packages).
When you install them, npm downloads them to your project.

e.g.    npm init                        --> initalise an application from NPM
/       npm install express mongoose    --> to install express and mongoose for project.
/       import express from "express"   --> to use express
/       import mongoose from "mongoose" --> to use mongoose

when we do npm init an application is started from the npm and then asks for the basic details
such as name , description , keywords etc.